Swiss Franc Gains Versus Peers as Falling Asian Stocks Spur Safety Demand

-- B y   M a s a k i   K o n d o
-- 
2011-09-02T03:32:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/swiss-franc-gains-versus-peers-as-falling-asian-stocks-spur-safety-demand.html
The Swiss franc gained against all
of its 16 major counterparts as falling stocks boosted demand
for safer assets. The franc climbed to as high as 1.12929 per
euro, the strongest level since Aug. 22, before trading at
1.12968 as of 12:31 p.m. in  Tokyo .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Naoto Hosoda at 
 nhosoda@bloomberg.net  